pipeline_summary.name: climate_data_fusion_pipeline
pipeline_summary.description: Implements a climate data fusion workflow that downloads weather station data from five meteorological agencies, normalizes each dataset, and merges them into a unified climate dataset.

components.name: Download NOAA Weather Data
components.description: Downloads NOAA weather station CSV data from the FTP endpoint and passes it via XCom.

components.name: Download ECMWF Weather Data
components.description: Downloads ECMWF weather station CSV data from the HTTPS endpoint and passes it via XCom.

components.name: Download JMA Weather Data
components.description: Downloads JMA weather station CSV data from the HTTPS endpoint and passes it via XCom.

components.name: Download MetOffice Weather Data
components.description: Downloads MetOffice weather station CSV data from the HTTPS endpoint and passes it via XCom.

components.name: Download BOM Weather Data
components.description: Downloads BOM weather station CSV data from the HTTPS endpoint and passes it via XCom.

components.name: Normalize NOAA Weather Data
components.description: Converts NOAA raw CSV data to a standard format (ISO timestamp, Celsius temperature, meters elevation).

components.name: Normalize ECMWF Weather Data
components.description: Converts ECMWF raw CSV data to a standard format (ISO timestamp, Celsius temperature, meters elevation).

components.name: Normalize JMA Weather Data
components.description: Converts JMA raw CSV data to a standard format (ISO timestamp, Celsius temperature, meters elevation).

components.name: Normalize MetOffice Weather Data
components.description: Converts MetOffice raw CSV data to a standard format (ISO timestamp, Celsius temperature, meters elevation).

components.name: Normalize BOM Weather Data
components.description: Converts BOM raw CSV data to a standard format (ISO timestamp, Celsius temperature, meters elevation).

components.name: Merge Climate Datasets
components.description: Merges the five normalized climate datasets into a unified Parquet dataset with a standardized schema.

upstream_policy.description: Executes after all five normalization tasks complete successfully.

description.default: Implements a climate data fusion workflow that downloads weather station data from five meteorological agencies, normalizes each dataset, and merges them into a unified climate dataset.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

connections.name: Local Filesystem for Final Parquet Output

sources: NOAA weather station CSV from ftp://noaa.gov/weather/stations.csv
ECMWF weather station CSV from https://ecmwf.int/data/stations.csv
JMA weather station CSV from https://jma.go.jp/weather/stations.csv
sinks: Unified climate dataset in Parquet format stored on local filesystem (/tmp/climate_pipeline/unified_climate_dataset.parquet)
